Scythris pollicella is a moth of the family Scythrididae. It was described by Bengt Å. Bengtsson in 2002. It is found in Oman and Yemen.The wingspan is 10–11.5 mm. The head, labial palpi, antennae, collar, tegulae, thorax, legs and forewings are beige or bone coloured, the antennae with rather long cilia. The hindwings are pale fuscous.